⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Sutty
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Sutty:U1:4d2d94⟧

WHO   — Sutty — the Observer who recovered the Telling
WHAT  — An Ekumen Observer on Aka, a world that erased its own past in a frenzy of forced modernization — and the outsider who climbs into the high country to find the outlawed wisdom called the Telling.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: Hainish Cycle  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a people that burns its own books and forbids its own stories starves the spirit it claims to feed; because what is silenced does not die, it goes underground and waits to be heard.
HOW   — By listening rather than ruling — by learning the maz, the old story-tellers, by reading the proscribed ideograms, and by carrying the Telling out of hiding without betraying those who kept it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  A people that burns its own stories does not erase them — it only teaches them to whisper, and waits for someone to listen.

